{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>We recently finished the first phase of the <a href=\"https://next.gatsbyjs.org/showcase/\">Site Showcase</a>, which is a searchable, filterable library of sites built with Gatsby!</p>\n<p>We’re starting the second phase soon and would love your help! For a list of tasks that need to be done, see <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/issues/5927\">Issue #5927</a>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"featured-sites.png\" alt=\"Featured Sites\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"filtered-sites.png\" alt=\"Filtered Sites\"></p>\n<p>The Site Showcase was developed by Cassie Beckley (<a href=\"https://github.com/ThatOtherPerson\">@ThatOtherPerson</a>), Shawn Wang (<a href=\"https://github.com/sw-yx\">@sw-yx</a>), and Kurt Kemple (<a href=\"https://github.com/kkemple\">@kkemple</a>) and Flo (<a href=\"https://github.com/fk\">@fk</a>) did an <em>incredible</em> job on design. Many thanks to other people who contributed, including Kyle Gill (<a href=\"https://github.com/gillkyle\">@gillkyle</a>), LekoArts (<a href=\"https://github.com/LeKoArts\">@LeKoArts</a>), David Luhr (<a href=\"https://github.com/davidluhr\">@davidluhr</a>), Vince P. (<a href=\"https://github.com/daydream05\">@daydream05</a>), Mike Allanson (<a href=\"https://github.com/m-allanson\">@m-allanson</a>), Michal Piechowiak (<a href=\"https://github.com/pieh\">@pieh</a>), Sam Bhagwat (<a href=\"https://github.com/calcsam\">@calcsam</a>) and more.</p>\n<h2 id=\"submitting-your-site\"><a href=\"#submitting-your-site\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Submitting your site</h2>\n<p>If you’ve built a site with Gatsby and would like it to appear in the Site Showcase, please <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/site-showcase-submissions.md\">submit your site</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"why-build-a-site-showcase\"><a href=\"#why-build-a-site-showcase\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Why build a site showcase?</h2>\n<p>We built the showcase to make it easier for you to (1) find the source code for open source Gatsby sites and (2) show off Gatsby to clients, coworkers, friends &#x26; family.</p>\n<h3 id=\"source-code\"><a href=\"#source-code\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Source code</h3>\n<p>Sometimes, an example is worth 1000 words. That’s why we added a GitHub icon next to sites with open source code (not all sites will have this icon).</p>\n<p><img src=\"site-showcase-source-code.png\" alt=\"Site Showcase Source Code Available Icon\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"showing-off-what-gatsby-can-do\"><a href=\"#showing-off-what-gatsby-can-do\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Showing off what Gatsby can do</h3>\n<p>The Site Showcase can help you pitch Gatsby to clients and coworkers as the best option for their next project because it shows what developers can accomplish with Gatsby.</p>\n<h2 id=\"ux-research-process\"><a href=\"#ux-research-process\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>UX research process</h2>\n<p>Many of you contributed to the discussion and development of the site showcase. Here are the intial issue and PR if you’d like to go through the discussion that led to this project:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/issues/4392\">Site Showcase Issue</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/pull/5524\">Site Showcase WIP PR</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"empathy-map\"><a href=\"#empathy-map\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Empathy map</h3>\n<p>Here’s a summary of what I learned from over 80 interviews with Gatsby users. This “empathy map” describes what kinds of pain points we’re trying to solve with the site showcase.</p>\n<p><img src=\"empathy-map-site-showcase.jpg\" alt=\"Empathy Map Site Showcase\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"user-flow\"><a href=\"#user-flow\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>User Flow</h3>\n<p>The empathy map reflects the following pain points:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the Awesome Gatsby list of sites (used to be part of the READme in the open source repo) was growing long and was not searchable or filterable</li>\n<li>the Awesome Gatsby list also had no visual indication of what the sites looked like</li>\n<li>there isn’t enough time or room for everyone’s awesome sites to get retweeted by the @Gatsbyjs account</li>\n</ul>\n<p>With the empathy map and the interviews as our guide, we created a list of jobs to be done and imagined the typical flow a user would take through the site showcase. We did this to make sure we planned both a sensible information architecture and the necessary functionality to meet user’s main needs.</p>\n<p><img src=\"user-flow-site-showcase.jpg\" alt=\"User flow\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"defining-the-mvp\"><a href=\"#defining-the-mvp\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Defining the MVP</h3>\n<p>Based on the process described above, we thought the following features were important to include:</p>\n<p>Users should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" checked disabled> See screenshots of sites built with Gatsby (Landing page)</li>\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" checked disabled> See source code (Site detail page)</li>\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" checked disabled> Share sites by copying the URL</li>\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" checked disabled> Filter by category</li>\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" checked disabled> Search sites</li>\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" checked disabled> Submit their own site to the showcase through yaml file (Shannon writes the instructions)</li>\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" checked disabled> See featured sites</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"ways-you-can-help\"><a href=\"#ways-you-can-help\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Ways you can help</h2>\n<h3 id=\"future-iterations\"><a href=\"#future-iterations\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Future iterations</h3>\n<p>Here’s what’s next in <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/issues/5927\">Issue #5927</a>. Feel free to tackle any part of this project and contribute to it or discuss new possibilities!</p>\n<h2 id=\"sneak-peak-into-the-next-ux-project\"><a href=\"#sneak-peak-into-the-next-ux-project\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Sneak peak into the next UX project</h2>\n<p>Our next UX project is finishing up the starter showcase, which will look similar to the site showcase and also have a major functional difference: filter by dependency. Please contribute to these issues to help out!</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/issues/5334\">Starter Showcase Issue</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/pull/5831\">Starter Showcase WIP PR</a>\nAgain, many thanks to all the community members who have contributed to this research and to making Gatsby awesome. Stay tuned for updates on the site showcase and future Gatsby UX research projects!</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://twitter.com/shannonb_ux/status/938551014956732418\">Contact me</a> here if you have feedback that differs from or provides deeper insight into one of the pain points this article mentions.</li>\n<li>Follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/gatsbyjs\">Twitter</a>.</li>\n</ul>","excerpt":"We recently finished the first phase of the  Site Showcase , which is a searchable, filterable library of sites built with Gatsby! We’re…","timeToRead":4,"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2018-07-20-why-we-built-the-site-showcase/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Why We Created the Site Showcase","excerpt":null,"date":"July 20th 2018","rawDate":"2018-07-20T00:00:00.000Z","canonicalLink":null,"publishedAt":null,"tags":["documentation","launch"],"image":null,"imageAuthor":null,"imageAuthorLink":null,"imageTitle":null,"showImageInArticle":null,"author":{"id":"Shannon Soper","bio":"UX researcher and educational psychology fan. Teaches piano and keeps up with her dog's Instagram fans @dgtrwatson.","twitter":"@shannonb_ux","avatar":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='30' height='30' viewBox='0 0 30 30' version='1'%3e%3crect width='100%25' height='100%25' fill='%23f6f2f8'/%3e%3cpath d='M3 1C0 2-1 5 2 8v3c-1 3-1 3 3 3l4 1h2l1-2c-1-2 1-4 4-4 4 0 4 12 0 13-2 0-2 1-1 1v3c-3 4-2 4 4 4 5 0 6 0 6-2h1l2 2c2 0 2-1 2-7 0-7 0-7-3-8-4-2-4-3 0-3l3-2h-3l-3-1 3-1c3 0 4-1 4-5V1L19 0 3 1m9 4L8 6l8 1 4 1h1c1 0-2-4-4-4l-5 1M9 18v10c0 2 0 2 1 0 2-4 2-6 1-6l-1-3c0-2-1-2-1-1m14 4c-1 4-1 5 1 3h4l-1-1-2-2v-3l-2 3M6 23v2H5c-2-1-2-1-2 1s4 4 4 3c1-1-1-7-1-6' fill='%23e0d6eb' fill-rule='evenodd'/%3e%3c/svg%3e","width":63,"height":63,"src":"/static/shannon-soper-1ba762d97172909d581008b0561b9627-eb2ad.jpg","srcSet":"/static/shannon-soper-1ba762d97